The paper deals with computer vision techniques for instrument segmentation and tracking in the context of robotic and conventional laparoscopic surgery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of robotic systems, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning approaches indicates a possible categorization under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the comparison and evaluation of different methods, which suggests a possible categorization under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
